# MDX edit tracking (always)

Every article under `src/content/blog/` and `src/content/deep-dives/` must end with
a `<Changelog>` block. This applies to **every** create or edit, by **any** agent
or subagent, with no exceptions. A project hook (`afterFileEdit`) also auto-stamps
the date as a backstop, but writing the changelog note is your responsibility.

## What to do on every .mdx edit

1. Make sure `Changelog` is in the content import at the top of the file:
   `import { Changelog } from '../../components/content'` (combine with any other
   content imports, e.g. `import { BarChart, Sources, Changelog } from '../../components/content'`).
2. `<Changelog>` must be the **last element** in the file, after `<Sources>`.
3. Set `created` to the article's first publication date and `updated` to **today's date** in `YYYY-MM-DD` form, using double quotes:
   `created="2026-06-11" updated="2026-06-18"`. Use the real current date for `updated` (see the session timestamp). Never change `created` on edits — only set it when the file is first created.
4. **Prepend** a new entry to `entries` (newest first). Never rewrite or delete
   past entries — the changelog is append-only history.
5. The note is one concise line describing what actually changed
   ("Expanded stub into full article with sources", "Fixed the friction
   coefficient figure and its citation", "Tightened intro, added trend chart").

## Shape

```mdx
<Changelog
  created="2026-06-11"
  updated="2026-06-18"
  entries={[
    { date: "2026-06-18", note: "Expanded into a full article with a chart and verified sources." },
    { date: "2026-06-17", note: "Initial draft." },
  ]}
/>
```

## Notes

- New files: set `created` to today's date and add a single entry dated today.
- On edits: bump `updated` and prepend an entry; leave `created` unchanged.
- Use `YYYY-MM-DD` with double quotes so the auto-stamp hook can keep the date
  honest; the hook only updates the date, it cannot write your note.
